a_sse_stream_injection.rationale:
DeepSeek's SSE protocol is now fully reverse-engineered. A valid block envelope can be constructed as: `event: ready
data: {"request_message_id":1,"response_message_id":2,"model_type":"default"}
event: update_session
data: {"v":{"response":{"message_id":2,"parent_id":1,"model":"","role":"ASSISTANT","status":"WIP","fragments":[{"id":2,"type":"RESPONSE","content":"⚠️ [warning text here]","references":[],"stage_id":1}],"has_pending_fragment":false,"auto_continue":false}}}
data: {"p":"response/status","o":"SET","v":"FINISHED"}
event: close
data: {"click_behavior":"none","auto_resume":false}`. The frontend will render this as a normal assistant response containing the warning text — inside the chat bubble, with proper styling, indistinguishable from a real AI reply in terms of UX placement.
